\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces Scaling relations analysis of 24\nobreakspace  {}Herschel filaments. Panel\nobreakspace  {}A shows the velocity dispersion versus mass/length relation with fitted power law. Panel\nobreakspace  {}B shows the width distribution. The measured virial slope ($0.0812 \pm 0.0043$) differs from the theoretical prediction (0.0927) by $2.7\sigma $, while the universal width ($0.098 \pm 0.019$\nobreakspace  {}pc) is consistent with the characteristic dissipation scale in molecular clouds.}}{5}{figure.1}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:scaling}{{1}{5}{Scaling relations analysis of 24~Herschel filaments. Panel~A shows the velocity dispersion versus mass/length relation with fitted power law. Panel~B shows the width distribution. The measured virial slope ($0.0812 \pm 0.0043$) differs from the theoretical prediction (0.0927) by $2.7\sigma $, while the universal width ($0.098 \pm 0.019$~pc) is consistent with the characteristic dissipation scale in molecular clouds}{figure.1}{}}
